  <title>Eurotalk Interactive:Digital Tools for Rural Schools</title>
  <description>This project will provide teachers in rural schools with the latest digital technology on &quot;smart&quot; mobile phones, building on a successful pilot supported by the Ministry of Education which tested the use of interactive video learning. Eurotalk will update their existing educational software into Chichewa and write new lessons in line with existing curriculum. All software will be preinstalled onto the 100 handheld digital devices that will be distributed across the 50 schools selected. Working in partnership with the Scottish Malawi Foundation, Eurotalk will instruct staff on the use of the new technology, through weekly cluster meetings .</description>
